title: SN9
description: Three Raptor engines, including SN49. SpaceX has released a statement confirming that SN9 is up next for a high-altitude hop attempt, the planned altitude is not yet known.
notes: On 11 December 2020, SN9's stand inside SpaceX's High Bay malfunctioned, which tilted the vehicle, resulting in damage to both the forward and aft flaps on one side. SpaceX brought the vehicle upright and replaced the affected flaps.
SN9 was moved to the launch site on 22 December 2020.
SN9 has conducted one pressure test on 28 December 2020.
As of 13 January 2021, SN9 has conducted one cryogenic proof and four static fires.
